CREDITS

Peter Keller (psilord) <psilord@cs.wisc.edu>
For helping me understand how to use matrices and answering my countless
questions. I seriously would not have given OpenGL a chance, or would have
given up quickly if not for his passed down knowledge.
Also for his beautiful code this game was inspired by located at:
https://github.com/psilord/option-9

Amit Patel (amitp) <amitp@cs.stanford.edu>
For his extensive research related to hexagon grids, with in-depth explanations
located at: http://www.redblobgames.com/grids/hexagons/
Also for being kind enough to answer some questions I had via email regarding
hexagon algorithms.

(3b) <https://github.com/3b>
For maintaining Common Lisp bindings to OpenGL, and answering many questions I
had during early development.

Also worth mentioning:
The countless folks in #lispgames, #OpenGL, and #gamedev on Freenode IRC that
helped me with miscellaneous problems and encouraged me along the way.
